Hi Amanu and Sol,

I would caution against that recommendation because of the attached study that compared cloth mask vs medical masks. Moisture retention, reusability of cloth masks and poor circulation might be the reason for the increased risk of infection. Unfortunately there was no comparison of cloth mask with NO mask (IRB concluded it was unethical), which makes sense.

elements.text:
Hi Amanu and Sol,

I would caution against that recommendation because of the attached study that compared cloth mask vs medical masks. Moisture retention, reusability of cloth masks and poor circulation might be the reason for the increased risk of infection. Unfortunately there was no comparison of cloth mask with NO mask (IRB concluded it was unethical), which makes sense.

<@U010APHG8Q1> <@U010X37NPEJ> - The study is a comparison of a medical mask versus cloth. Unfortunately, the situation we are in right now doesn't offer the luxury of a medical mask. If used in addition to a medical mask, the cloth can add more protection and that can be changed/washed more frequently. 100% cotton - which is available in Ethiopia and other materials that offer filtration can be added in this dire siltation.
